The paper discusses data structures for dynamic closest pair problems, which are fundamental problems in computational geometry and data analysis. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also applies the data structures to hierarchical clustering, TSP heuristics, and machine learning, indicating potential relevance to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
